    "Summerfield Johnston Jr. inherited his family's Coca-Cola bottling franchise, Johnston Coca-Cola.",
    "He grew it into the largest independent Coke bottler by 1991, when the beverage giant's own bottler, Coca-Cola Enterprises, bought the business and tapped Johnson Jr. to run the combined operations.",
    "Johnston Jr. was CEO until 2001, turning the company around by decentralizing operations and empowering local bottlers. He retired as chairman in 2007.",
    "Johnston Jr. Plays polo and was inducted into the Museum of Polo Hall of Fame in 2001.",
    "His son, Summerfield III, died tragically in a 2007 polo accident."
